<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - 5 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS SPICER ES62-5A, ES62-5D, ES67-5A AND
        ES67-5D - DISASSEMBLY - MAINSHAFT
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="disassemble" graphiccount="14">
        <title>MAINSHAFT</title>
        <para>Refer to
            <hotlnk xrefid="f1301026">Figure 26</hotlnk>.
        </para>
        <figure id="f1301026" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1301026" filename="../figg13/G1301026.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0" resolution="72"/>
            <caption>Figure 26. Mainshaft Exploded View</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. BAFFLE</callout1>
                <callout1>2. SPACER</callout1>
                <callout1>3. BEARING CUP</callout1>
                <callout1>4. BEARING CONE</callout1>
                <callout1>5. MAIN DRIVE GEAR</callout1>
                <callout1>6. POCKET BEARING</callout1>
                <callout1>7. 1ST SPEED GEAR</callout1>
                <callout1>8. THRUST WASHER</callout1>
                <callout1>9. 2ND SPEED GEAR</callout1>
                <callout1>10. 2ND-3RD SPEED SYNCHRONIZER</callout1>
                <callout1>11. 3RD SPEED GEAR</callout1>
                <callout1>12. 4TH SPEED GEAR</callout1>
                <callout1>13. 4TH-5TH SPEED SYNCHRONIZER</callout1>
                <callout1>14. SNAP RING</callout1>
                <callout1>15. 2ND-3RD SPEED CLUTCH GEAR</callout1>
                <callout1>16. LOOSE NEEDLE BEARINGS, 2ND GEAR</callout1>
                <callout1>17. BEARING</callout1>
                <callout1>18. WASHER</callout1>
                <callout1>19. SPEEDOMETER GEAR OR SIGNAL GEAR</callout1>
                <callout1>20. REVERSE GEAR</callout1>
                <callout1>21. 1ST-REVERSE CLUTCH GEAR</callout1>
                <callout1>22. MAINSHAFT</callout1>
                <callout1>23. FLANGE OR END YOKE</callout1>
                <callout1>24. NUT</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place the mainshaft on a bench (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301027">Figure 27</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301027" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301027" filename="../figg13/G1301027.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 27. Place Mainshaft on Bench</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Wearing safety glasses, remove the output bearing (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301028">Figure 28</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301028" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301028" filename="../figg13/G1301028.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 28. Remove Output Bearing</caption>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>Wear safety glasses to prevent possible personal injury from flying metal pieces.</para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the bearing cone, thrust washer, reverse gear, and bearing (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301029">Figure 29</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301029" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301029" filename="../figg13/G1301029.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 29. Remove Bearing Cone, Thrust Washer, Reverse Gear, and Bearing</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove 1st-reverse clutch gear (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301030">Figure 30</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301030" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301030" filename="../figg13/G1301030.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 30. Remove 1st-Reverse Clutch Gear</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use a suitable puller to remove the pocket bearing (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301031">Figure 31</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301031" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301031" filename="../figg13/G1301031.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 31. Remove Pocket Bearing</caption>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>Do not pull on the synchronizer to remove the bearing. Doing so could damage the synchronizer
                        and cause shifting problems in the unit.
                    </para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the 4th-5th speed synchronizer (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301032">Figure 32</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301032" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301032" filename="../figg13/G1301032.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 32. Remove 4th-5th Speed Synchronizer</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the snap ring, 4th speed gear, and the washer from the mainshaft (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301033">Figure 33</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301033" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301033" filename="../figg13/G1301033.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 33. Remove Snap Ring, 4th Speed Gear, and Washer From Mainshaft</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove 3rd speed gear, thrust washer, and snap ring (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301034">Figure 34</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301034" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301034" filename="../figg13/G1301034.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 34. Remove 3rd Speed Gear, Thrust Washer, and Snap Ring</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the 2nd-3rd speed synchronizer next (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301035">Figure 35</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301035" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301035" filename="../figg13/G1301035.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 35. Remove 2nd-3rd Speed Synchronizer</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the snap ring and 2nd-3rd speed clutch gear (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301036">Figure 36</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301036" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301036" filename="../figg13/G1301036.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 36. Remove Snap Ring and 2nd-3rd Speed Clutch Gear</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Next, remove 2nd speed gear and the loose needle bearings that rest in the gear bore (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301037">Figure 37</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301037" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301037" filename="../figg13/G1301037.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 37. Remove 2nd Speed Gear and Loose Needle Bearings</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the snap ring, 1st speed gear, thrust washer and caged needle bearing (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301038">Figure 38</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301038" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301038" filename="../figg13/G1301038.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 38. Remove Snap Ring, 1st Speed Gear, Thrust Washer and Caged Needle Bearing</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Examine all parts for wear or damage. Inspect mainshaft gearlocks and synchronizer clutching
                teeth for excessive wear that could produce gear jumping (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301039">Figure 39</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301039" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301039" filename="../figg13/G1301039.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 39. Examine All Parts For Wear or Damage</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
